-- ICBC's 45 Billion Yuan Rights Offer Gets Approval From Chinese Regulator
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-05T12:46:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/icbc-s-45-billion-yuan-rights-offer-gets-approval-from-chinese-regulator.html
The  Industrial & Commercial Bank of
China  Ltd., the nation’s largest lender, received approval from
the securities regulator to sell as much as 45 billion yuan in a
rights offer, according to a statement posted on the regulator’s
website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
